<p>HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL 
Second session 
Agenda item 2 
</p>
<p><b>IMPLEMENTATION OF GENERAL ASSEMBLY RESOLUTION 60/251 
OF 15 MARCH 2006 ENTITLED &#8220;HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL&#8221; 
</b></p>
<p><b>Algeria, Benin, Cameroon, Cuba, Ghana, Lesotho</b>&#8727;<b>, Libyan Arab Jamahiriya, 
Mali, South Africa, Sudan and Zimbabwe</b>*<b>:  draft decision 
</b></p>
<p><b>2006/&#8230; Rectification of the status of the Committee on Economic, 
Social and Cultural Rights 
</b></p>
<p> <i>The Human Rights Council</i>, 
</p>
<p><i> Recalling </i>Economic and Social Council resolution 1985/17 of 28 May 1985 establishing 
the Committee on Economic, Social and Cultural Rights, 
</p>
<p> <i>Decides</i> to initiate at its third session a process proposing a legal framework to rectify the 
legal status of the Committee on Economic, Social and Cultural Rights by placing it on par with 
all other treaty monitoring bodies. 
</p>
<p>----- 
</p>
<p>                                                 
</p>
<p>&#8727;  Non-member States of the Human Rights Council. 
</p>
